Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Cut @sweet potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch
cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast until golden brown, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(peeled and minced). Strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves
off sprigs. Chop until you have 1 tsp of rosemary. Halve @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat
@chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook in pan until no longer pink in center, about
~{5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan to rest.

Add shallot, chopped rosemary, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} to same pan over
medium heat. Toss until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon}
and @fig jam{1%tablespoon} and simmer until syrupy, about ~{1%minute}. Add ½ cup water
and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Simmer until thickened, about ~{3%minutes}. Remove
pan from heat and swirl in @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Toss @arugula{2%ounce} in a #medium bowl{} with a squeeze of lemon and a drizzle of
@olive oil{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice chicken and serve next to arugula and potatoes. Drizzle with sauce.